\", \"show_in_menus\": false, \"search_description\": \"\", \"go_live_at\": null, \"expire_at\": null, \"expired\": false, \"locked\": false, \"locked_at\": null, \"locked_by\": null, \"first_published_at\": null, \"last_published_at\": null, \"latest_revision_created_at\": \"2021-12-02T22:27:31.398Z\", \"live_revision\": null, \"alias_of\": null, \"date\": \"2021-12-02\", \"verse\": \"<p data-block-key=\\\"esv9m\\\">Genesis 21 v 9- 19</p>\", \"body\": \"<p data-block-key=\\\"496xs\\\">Genesis 21 v 9- 19</p><p data-block-key=\\\"a7ae8\\\">Hagar faces a terrible time of rejection. Sarah became jealous of Ishmael, the son of Hagar the bond woman. She asked Abraham to send Hagar and her son away. saying that Ishmael was not going to have a share in her son&#x27;s inheritance. Abraham was troubled. it broke his heart to send his son away, but God said he should because He has a plan for Ishmael. Abraham listened to God and sent Hagar and Ishmael away. The word of God says that they wandered in the wilderness of Beer-sheba. We all know the dangers of the wilderness. There is no water, shelter, there are wild animals, bandits etc.</p><p data-block-key=\\\"3se3\\\">W=hile still wandering in the wilderness, the water got finished. She didn&#x27;t know what to do. she thought her child was going to die. she put the child under one of the shrubs, went away, for she said,let me not see the death of my child. sometimes we find ourselves in similar situations. The burdens of life become so heavy that we think we cannot bear them. David found himself in hopeless situation and he wanted to fly away. Psalm 55 v 1-8</p><p data-block-key=\\\"f5o1g\\\">Even when the burdens of life exceeds our ability to bear them, they never exceeds God&#x27;s ability. 2 Corinthians 1 v 9-10. Hagar should not have been worried, she had the promise of God that he was going to make Ishmael the father of a great nation. Gen 16 v 10-11. Sometimes life hurts so much that we forget the promises of God in our lives. What we fail to see is that our pain is the path God uses to fulfill the promises He has made to us.</p><p data-block-key=\\\"538lv\\\">the truth is the problems are going to come into our lives, and they will come unannounced and they will hurt us badly. so when they come, we must run to the Lord. He will hear us and He will help us. In verse 16, Hagar sat down and wept. we may ask ourselves why she didn&#x27;t pray. why cry instead of praying. Hagar didn&#x27;t know, but God had been there the whole time. He called her by her name. He won&#x27;t leave you either. You will never live one second of your life or take one step as a child of God without Him. Hebrews 13 v 5.</p><p data-block-key=\\\"192mv\\\">God opened her eyes and showed her what had been therein front of her all along. She saw a well. our problems blind us to His provisions.</p>\", \"wagtail_admin_comments\": [], \"gallery_images\": [{\"pk\": 7, \"sort_order\": 0, \"page\": 11, \"image\": \"photos/christsheep.jpg\", \"caption\": \"\"}]}',NULL,11,1),(67,0,'2022-02-25 11:29:19.794089','{\"pk\": 11, \"path\": \"0001000100010005\", \"depth\": 4, \"numchild\": 0, \"translation_key\": \"837b18ab-f41b-4221-9b4e-d90e58522469\", \"locale\": 1, \"title\": \"God has a plan for your life\", \"draft_title\": \"God has a plan for your life\", \"slug\": \"god-has-a-plan-for-your-life\", \"content_type\": 44, \"live\": false, \"has_unpublished_changes\": true, \"url_path\": \"/faith-daily-walk-with-god/devotionals/god-has-a-plan-for-your-life/\", \"owner\": 2, \"seo_title\": \"\", \"show_in_menus\": false, \"search_description\": \"\", \"go_live_at\": null, \"expire_at\": null, \"expired\": false, \"locked\": false, \"locked_at\": null, \"locked_by\": null, \"first_published_at\": null, \"last_published_at\": null, \"latest_revision_created_at\": \"2022-02-25T11:28:53.611Z\", \"live_revision\": null, \"alias_of\": null, \"date\": \"2021-12-02\", \"verse\": \"<p data-block-key=\\\"esv9m\\\">Genesis 21 v 9- 