ife by one, Jesus Christ (Romans 5:17).</p><p data-block-key=\\\"2tl3a\\\"></p><p data-block-key=\\\"kf8e\\\">Righteousness is the nature of God that describes His Rightness; His ability to do and be right always. That same nature is imparted to your spirit when you receive Christ into your heart to be born again. Then, you&#x27;re automatically brought into oneness with God; His character of rightness is wrought in your spirit. The result of this is that you can stand in God&#x27;s presence with boldness, without condemnation, inferiority or guilt; because you&#x27;ve become the righteousness of God in Christ Jesus (2 Corinthians 5:21).</p><p data-block-key=\\\"75jpm\\\">God expects you to live this life of righteousness daily. Your life should be the expression of the life He&#x27;s given you. For example, when a child is born, he is naturally human; but he starts building and developing his innate human characteristics. He doesn&#x27;t have the nature of a dog or camel, but of a human being. But he must develop that nature through knowledge and fellowship with other humans. In the same way, when you become a child of God, you automatically receive the righteousness of God. Even if you err, it wouldn&#x27;t be because you&#x27;re no longer righteous, but because you haven&#x27;t grown or matured in the knowledge of God. A child, who&#x27;s not taught how to walk, may never walk; not because he doesn&#x27;t have the ability to walk but because he was never taught. Likewise, to grow as a mature Christian and be able to live righteously to the glory of God, you must be taught to live by God&#x27;s Word.</p><p data-block-key=\\\"2cggp\\\">This is one of the reasons you must become a committed member of a local church. In church, you&#x27;re taught how to live the life of righteousness which you&#x27;ve received in Christ Jesus. As you live out that righteousness, many will witness the perfection and inner beauty of divinity in you; God&#x27;s nature of rightness, excellence, and perfection will be manifested in everything you do.</p>\", \"wagtail_admin_comments\": [], \"gallery_images\": [{\"pk\": 6, \"sort_order\": 0, \"page\": 10, \"image\": \"photos/login.jpg\", \"caption\": \"\"}]}',NULL,10,1),(69,0,'2022-02-25 11:46:09.879893','{\"pk\": 5, \"path\": \"00010001\", \"depth\": 2, \"numchild\": 4, \"translation_key\": \"62b12729-7c79-4fab-95c8-74ba64f379e3\", \"locale\": 1, \"title\": \"Faith - daily walk with God\", \"draft_title\": \"Faith - daily walk with God\", \"slug\": \"faith-daily-walk-with-god\", \"content_type\": 2, \"live\": true, \"has_unpublished_changes\": false, \"url_path\": \"/faith-daily-walk-with-god/\", \"owner\": 1, \"seo_title\": \"\", \"show_in_menus\": false, \"search_description\": \"\", \"go_live_at\": null, \"expire_at\": null, \"expired\": false, \"locked\": false, \"locked_at\": null, \"locked_by\": null, \"first_published_at\": \"2021-11-12T09:47:28.214Z\", \"last_published_at\": \"2021-11-30T10:54:59.538Z\", \"latest_revision_created_at\": \"2021-11-30T10:54:59.152Z\", \"live_revision\": 32, \"alias_of\": null, \"body\": \"<p data-block-key=\\\"acp7e\\\">Welcome to faithwalk</p>\", \"header\": 1, \"featured_posts_sub_heading\": \"Love is one of the most important principles of a Christian\'s life; our Lord Jesus specifically commanded us to love one another.\", \"wagtail_admin_comments\": [], \"featured_posts\": [{\"pk\": null, \"sort_order\": 0, \"page\": 5, \"post\": 12}, {\"pk\": null, \"sort_order\": 1, \"page\": 5, \"post\": 13}]}',NULL,5,1),(70,0,'2022-02-25 12:55:13.604144','{\"pk\": 10, \"path\": \"0001000100010004\", \"depth\": 4, \"numchild\": 0, \"translation_key\": \"1d3506ef-9297-449c-8fb5-da982da63f56\", \"locale\": 1, \"title\": \"The Righteousness Of God In You\", \"draft_title\": \"The Righteousness Of God In You\", \"slug\": \"the-righteousness-of-god-in-you\", \"content_type\": 44, \"live\": true, \"has_unpublished_changes\": true, \"url_path\": \"/faith-daily-walk-with-god/dev